        "Name": "Cazador",
        "Details": "The Cazador is the BattleMech version of the Reptar MilitiaMech developed by the Escorpión Imperio. Where the original Reptar mounted a fuel cell engine, the Imperio's technicians and engineers fitted a fusion engine with ten heat sinks to the endo steel chassis. Instead of the original protomech AC/8 with light machineguns in the side torsos, the Cazador has upgraded to a single LB 10-X mounted in the right arm and a small pulse laser mounted in each side torso. Two tons of autocannon ammunition is carried in a CASE protected bay in the right torso. Six tons of armor protects the 'Mech, while a supercharger is attached to the engine, allowing the Cazador to reach a top speed of 108 km/h in short bursts and facilitate quick escapes or pursuits.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
